   Even now that I am 55 I use the MS2 pet while soloing almost exclusively.  True  the 54 water pet regens quite nicely, and 53 air tanks ok, but the MS2 pet has huge hp, has MUCH better dmg aviodence then an earth pet, and if you keep summoning till you get one with a dmg shield its just sick.   After giving it armor it tanks insanely well.  <br>
   It is also the best pet for reclaim/medding, put on a summoning ef.3 item and (rough estimate using percentages) I get around 7-8% mana per reclaim (well over 100 mana/tick).  Its also my prefered pet for chaining mobs, as they have the same hp as earth but avoid dmg better.<br>
<br>
Just to add, I don't personal believe that pets regen at their normal rate when engaged so I would't knock the HP estimate down a few hundred.   I don't remember ever seeing pet's hp percentage increase while chasing fleeing mobs, maybe water pets a few times but even then at a rate slower then their normal regen.<br>
